The paper discusses the design and evaluation of a link layer security architecture for wireless sensor networks, which falls under the categories of computer networks (cs.NI), security and privacy (cs.CR), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also proposes a configurable software-based architecture, which involves programming and software engineering (cs.SE), and discusses the optimization of resources, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
